							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/caitlincowan/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Caitlin-Cowan-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Caitlin Cowan" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/caitlincowan/">Caitlin Cowan</a></h6>
										Caitlin Cowan is the author of <em>Happy Everything</em> (Cornerstone Press, 2024). She has taught writing at the University of North Texas, Texas Woman’s University, and Interlochen Center for the Arts. Caitlin works in arts nonprofit administration for Blue Lake Fine Arts Camp, where she serves as Director of International Programs and as Chair of Creative Writing. Caitlin also serves as Poetry Co-Editor at <em>Pleiades</em> and writes <em>PopPoetry</em>, a weekly poetry and pop culture newsletter. She lives on Michigan’s west coast with her husband, their young daughter, and two mischievous cats.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://caitlincowan.com" target="_blank" class="external">http://caitlincowan.com</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
